What does water restoration mean for people and nature? 💧 We asked our partners @bonnenviro, @audubonca, Colorado River Indian Tribes, @riverpartners, the Northwestern Band of the Shoshone Nation to explain what restoring water means to their specific mission.
 
Learn more about how we’re helping restore water – link in bio.
 
#ItsOurHome #WaterPositiveFuture

The water crisis looks different across the world. While some of us don’t see it yet, others see it every day.
 
We are working with partners on the ground, who have deep knowledge of local challenges and solutions, to support long-term projects that improve, maintain or protect freshwater resources. We recently announced a comprehensive strategy to help build a #WaterPositiveFuture for people and nature that includes restoring water in 18 water-stressed areas around the world.
 
While there’s no single solution, the benefits of each project go beyond the drops of water. The positive impacts of one project ripple across ecosystems for people, nature and wildlife.
 
Learn more in the link in bio. #ItsOurHome

The pregnancy journey is often full of excitement, expectation, and joy, but for many Black moms, that’s not the full story. We believe every parent deserves to experience the full joy of pregnancy and beyond, which is why we’re proud to continue our work to help change these systemic issues that prevent Black moms from receiving equitable care and commit $250,000 over the next 12 months. For every share of our #RaiseCareDeliverJoy video in June, Pampers will donate an additional $1 to @birthequity so that every parent can live to experience the full joy of pregnancy and beyond (up to $10,000). Because only when we raise the quality of care, can we deliver more joy. 💛

This uniqueness is something we celebrate — during #PrideMonth and beyond — because we know when each of us shows up as our full selves, there's no limit to what we can achieve or the good we can do in the world.
 
There are as many P&G+Me stories as there are employees; hit that link in bio to learn more about P&G + Me = Mutual Success

We’re dedicating our #WaterWednesday to six new projects we are supporting in Utah and Idaho that improve, manage, and protect water resources for people and nature. 

At P&G, we’re leveraging our resources to help tackle water challenges in water-stressed areas where we operate and in consumers’ homes. That’s why we’re partnering with @bonnenviro to support the Wuda Ogwa Water and Habitat Eco-Restoration project in direct collaboration with the Northwestern Band of the Shoshone Nation. 

This project aims to recover and improve a mile of habitat along Battle Creek, ultimately restoring the natural ecosystems and enhancing water quality for the community. 

Tap the link in bio to learn more. #ItsOurHome #WaterPositiveFuture

How can we prevent recyclable items from literally falling through the cracks? ♻️ 

It’s been a mission that Juan Bonilla, Director of Personal Health Care Sustainability, and his team have been focused on for years. 

They’re tackling a big recycling challenge—making sure small items like travel-size bottles and toothbrushes don’t get missed in recycling systems. 

By collaborating with @closed_loop and @recyclingpartnership, Juan and his team are advancing technology and expanding collection programs to create stronger markets for small plastics and boost recycling rates nationwide.

“Our goal is to leverage P&G’s scale to collaborate with other companies to drive industry-wide, systemic solutions,” Juan says. 

Learn more about our broader work to advance a more circular future via the link in our bio. 

#PGEmployee #MeetOurPeople #ItsOurHome #Sustainability

✨ Meet @JordanHarkins a full-time colleague who started her P&G career journey a few years ago as one of our incredible summer interns! ✨

Reflecting on her experience, Jordan says, "As an intern, I was truly impressed by the level of responsibility I was given at such a young age. The projects I worked on were not only impactful for the business but also personally meaningful to me. I remember thinking, 'There's no way I could be given even more significant work!'" 

At P&G, our interns don’t just observe — they lead! 🚀 Whether launching innovative products or shaping the future of our iconic brands, they make a meaningful impact from Day 1.

Tap the link in our bio to learn more about our internship program! 

#PGandMe #Internship #CareerGrowth #FutureLeaders

The future of dishwashing is here, and these are the people making it happen! ✨ 

Jill Bos and Katie King are R&D scientists and the P&G innovators behind Dawn Powersuds! 🫧 

They’re dedicated to making dishwashing easier and more satisfying with a formula that keeps suds whiter and longer lasting, ensuring your dishes shine brighter and dry faster! 

Curiosity, problem-solving, and a passion for impact? Learn more at the link in our bio! #PGInnovation

Meet Fernanda from Cedros, Honduras, whose story shows how access to clean water can transform lives. 🙌 

Thanks to the #PowerOfCleanWater, millions of children around the world are staying healthy, attending school, and pursuing their dreams. For Fernanda, that means becoming a teacher someday. 📚 

For over 20 years, P&G has worked with dedicated partners to deliver more than 24 billion liters of clean water to communities in over 100 countries through the Children’s Safe Drinking Water Program. 

Learn more about the program’s impact at the link in bio. #ActsOfGood

Experience the power of Trap & Lock Technology with PowerSuds!

This innovative formula from @DawnDishWash delivers double the suds, ensuring superior grease removal from start to finish. 🙌 

This game-changer came from listening to you and your dishwashing struggles. Say goodbye to constant refills and hello to easier, more efficient washing! 🍽️✨ 

Tap the link in our bio to learn more about this #PGInnovation. #DawnPowerSuds #DoubleTheSuds #DawnDishSoap
